// Phase-4 PostToolUse guardrail — READY TO ENABLE (not auto-applied).
//
// The automation build deliberately did NOT self-edit .claude/settings.json: adding a
// startup hook is self-modification of the agent's own config, which the ROADMAP flags
// as an open decision needing Vic's explicit ok (and the harness classifier blocks it).
//
// To enable: merge the "hooks" block below into .claude/settings.json (keep your existing
// "enabledPlugins"). The hook runs automation/scripts/hook_postwrite.sh after every
// Edit/Write/MultiEdit; for a wiki/ page it runs the FAST single-file hygiene quick-check
// (the page's links resolve + it's in index.md) and logs to automation/logs/hook.log.
// READ-ONLY, non-blocking (always exits 0). Disable by removing this block.
//
// Tested working: `echo '{"tool_input":{"file_path":".../wiki/themes/power-semis.md"}}'
//                  | automation/scripts/hook_postwrite.sh`  → caught the [[Canonical]] typo.
{
  "hooks": {
    "PostToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Edit|MultiEdit|Write",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "/Users/victor_he/Projects/stocks-wiki/automation/scripts/hook_postwrite.sh"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
